The paper discusses beamforming schemes for millimeter wave (mmW) cellular networks, which are a topic of interest in the networking and communication fields. The paper specifically focuses on energy consumption, which is a concern in the design of wireless systems and falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of analog-to-digital converters (ADCs) and phase shifters, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of context information (CI) and proposes a new signaling structure, which are topics related to system design and control (cs.SY) and architecture (cs.AR).
